Constructor:
      Constructor is a block of code that is used to construct object.

Why we use constructor:

      Constructor help us initialize object in cleaner and more readable way.
      They are better that mehtods becuse they are called automatically when we crate an objct.
      Most of the time fielda are private and becuse of this reason we cant access them out sid of
      the class in which they are declerd and cant initialize them .

How to use Constructor:

     we create constructor by writing a block of code that has same name as class name when we create of
     the object of the class and it is called automatically.

Rules:
1)   Constructors dont have return types not even void
2)   Constructors shoud have same name as class name.
3)   Constructors can have access modifiers like private public and protected .
4)   Constructors can not have non access modifies like static final synchronized
5)   Default constructor is provided by java if we dont write one
6)   when we create the object of class then constructor is call
if the class name is Dog Dog do1=new Dog();
7)   We can create mutltiple construtors to give the other use flexibility that they dont have
to privide all the values to all the instance feild when creating an object of our class.
8)  we can call the constroctor of al class by using this keyword with parenthesis.
this() we can pass parameters and java will decide base on these parameters which constructor to call.
"this " keyword:
when ever we can same name varibles as instance varible and local varibles this keyword can help us resolve
the conflict between local and instance variable.

class human{
String name="sleeping zombi;
