what is inheritance:
     inheritance is a machanism in java throught which we can get the properties and methods from the
     parent class inside the child class.

     inheritance helps us reduce the amount of code that we have to write for example if there are some property
     and methods which are present in many different clasess we can create a parent class for all of those
     properties and can put the common properties or method inside that parent class and can make chidern clasess
     extand from that parent class.
1) create a parent class
2) put all the common methods and properties from childern  clasess inside that parent class.
3) use extands keyword to inherit from that parent class.

Rules:

1) private fields and private mehtods can not be inherited inside the childminder class.














